Quote:One of those great research tidbits recently was that knowing a plotline makes people enjoy a movie more.That's bullshit for most stories. There's nothing like going into a movie (or book) with no foreknowledge and being completely blown away. It's rare these days, and something to be worked towards if at all possible. The Matrix, Fight Club, Inception, all of those wouldn't have been nearly as awesome if I had known all about them going in.If you already know roughly what happens, you spend the entire movie internally wondering "is this where ____ happens?" "what about now? no. Now?". That destroys the experience.
