I happen to agree with you, but that's not what the research found. For some things, I don't care. For example, I've recently discovered the short-story collections of Sherlock Holmes books free on Kindle (highly recommended, BTW). I know that the case will be solved. There's no harm in knowing that, because that's just what he does. It's the *how* that is the story.On the other hand, when it comes to Prometheus, I'm not reading any of these spoilers until I have a chance to re-watch the first two movies .
