Saint wrote:It's ironic that prequels to movies from the 80s always look way newer than the films that allegedly took place "later" than it.I know it bothers some but it never bothers me at all. Advances in our own technology inform our vision of the future and if a prequel is written significantly after the original work *and* is supposed to be based in our reality, then it only makes sense to me to see what sometimes looks like more advanced tech in the prequels.Though the argument I've heard from some for Prometheus looking more advanced than anything we see in ships from Alien or Aliens is that this is the first *science* ship we've seen on screen, instead of a heavy freighter or a troop transport.
