Pokrface wrote:* It's always been assumed that the reason the Nostromo is diverted to LV-426 to pick up the alien is because WY had previously intercepted the same transmission Dallas mentions at the beginning of Alien, and then arranged for the next available ship (the Nostromo) to pop down and check it out. If Prometheus takes place on LV-426, then WY has advanced knowledge of exactly what's down there.WY definitely knew exactly what was down there. If you recall, the Nostromo's computer had a secret directive for "Science Officer's Eyes Only." It was something like, "First priority: retrieve organism. All other priorities secondary. Crew expendable." Also note that Dallas said that Ash (the android science officer) was brought on board just before liftoff (months before the movie starts). So the company knew what was down there a long time ago.
