Scott's been a bit chatty about Prometheus in the last couple of days, a few minor spoilers (don't read if you want to go in completely clean, of course):
Spoiler: show
- Prometheus takes place on LV-223, not LV-426 (but they're in the same system).- Charlize Theron is a real company suit, I guess she's the Carter Burke of the story in that case. When everyone is waking up from cryo, she apparently just asks if anyone died, in a cold manner. She also doesn't react to the process like the others, who are throwing up and can barely stand. She's doing pushups and got out on her own, while the others need help from David. Could he be the known android and Vickers the corporate safety measure?- There's a scene involving Shaw that will be a callback to the chestburster scene. (Shaw in the medlab, I guess?)- The Derelict on LV-426 didn't crash, according to Scott. It landed there.
Empire Q&A can be found here: http://www.empireonline.com/interviews/ ... p?IID=1490
