Bagheera wrote:Pokrface wrote:* It's always been assumed that the reason the Nostromo is diverted to LV-426 to pick up the alien is because WY had previously intercepted the same transmission Dallas mentions at the beginning of Alien, and then arranged for the next available ship (the Nostromo) to pop down and check it out. If Prometheus takes place on LV-426, then WY has advanced knowledge of exactly what's down there.WY definitely knew exactly what was down there. If you recall, the Nostromo's computer had a secret directive for "Science Officer's Eyes Only." It was something like, "First priority: retrieve organism. All other priorities secondary. Crew expendable." Also note that Dallas said that Ash (the android science officer) was brought on board just before liftoff (months before the movie starts). So the company knew what was down there a long time ago.SPECIAL ORDER 937NOSTROMO REROUTED TO NEW COORDINATESINVESTIGATE LIFE FORMGATHER SPECIMENPRIORITY ONE - ENSURE RETURN OF ORGANISM FOR ANALYSISALL OTHER CONSIDERATIONS SECONDARYCREW EXPENDABLEAsh: "Bring back life form, priority one. All other priorities are rescinded."They knew a life form was down there, and Ash may or may not have had knowledge not gained through observation of the thing on the Nostromo. His "perfect organism" speech shows that he's either been observing it diligently, or he knows more about the alien from outside sources.Still, I don't believe there's enough canonical evidence (i.e., evidence explicitly presented on-screen) that WY knows any more than that there's "a lifeform" on LV426. That's knowledge that likely would have been gained through translating the derelict's warning, but we simply aren't given enough information to know for sure. We have to speculate. Prometheus will potentially fix the speculation through retcon.
