Posted: Wed Apr 18, 2012 4:24 pm
Keen wrote:DonRoberto wrote:I find this to be a great idea and one that I'm not sure I've ever seen in scifi. Ancient Aliens is a staple of sci-fi. Especially since Chariot of the Gods. The Ancients in Stargate did some mucking about with humans long ago. They likely seeded the galaxy with life, and made sure humans (as opposed to whatever intelligent species would have naturally evolved) evolved on Earth.Yeah I just like the idea that they're updating it for modern biological science. That is the idea is not "ancient aliens visited primordial Earth and seeded life" nor is it "ancient aliens came to Earth and gave early historical humans technology that enabled them to build pyramids, etc." instead it's "ancient aliens came to Earth and found higher apes that they tampered with genetically in subtle ways to form modern humans, and then left them to their own devices."I find the difference very satisfying from a scifi perspective.Some movies just grate me the wrong way, like The Matrix where the whole premise (harvesting humans for electrical power) is ridiculous. If a movie makes an effort to have scifi ideas I like them to be logical, either that or leave it fantastical or unexplained.
